description.narrative: UNICEF Jordan maintained regular and systematic field monitoring activities for the flagship projects across the country; providing technical support in collecting field data through assessments, surveys, phone calls, social media, and direct interviews. The field monitoring team collected and shared beneficiary feedbacks on the project design, implementation, and quality, contributing to enhancing the accountability of affected population (AAP). Through over 200 regular field monitoring visits to Makani centers, health clinics and public schools, a total of 1,200 observations, suggestions, and recommendations were generated with 40 per cent of the suggested actions implemented by the relevant program sections by August 2020. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:30/08/2020
